Head Elder
The scoop of the day
The latest updates
Once again, another
wonderful day in The
Community. Yesterday the
Year Twelves were assigned
their lifelong jobs, along with
the particularly important job
of The Receiver being
assigned to Jonas. Hopefully,
unlike the previous receiver,
he will not disappear.
More than a year ago, an unknown plane had
flown over The Community and forced it into a
lockdown for more than 10 minutes. No one
had been told at the time, but the plane had
crashed, and the pilot did not survive. No one
knows why the plane had flown over The
Community, but The Head Elder did confirm
that no damage was done and that no one
except the pilot was hurt. The technology was
taken out of the aircraft and used in some
experimental projects. The details of the
experimental projects have not yet been
released, but the elder responsible for the
projects has said that they will be used for the
good of the community
The plane that crashed over a year ago.
New technology being developed!
The Second Elder
An important
announcement
A quick reminder that all females
under nine must have their hair
ribbons neatly always tied. Please note
that objects are not to be removed
from the recreation area and that
snacks are to be eaten, not horded.
Remember to get tomorrows paper at
the news stand near The House of
The Old so you can get all the latest
news in The Community.

Second Elder for the information
